        "rendered": "Query Loop block"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Query Loop block</em> is an advanced block that allows you to display posts based on specified parameters, like a PHP loop without the code. You can think of it as a more complex and powerful <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/latest-posts-block/\"><em>Latest Posts Block</em></a>. With various block patterns integrated into the block setup, you can do things like create a portfolio or a page full of your favorite recipes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-main.png\" alt=\"Query loop block in the editor\" class=\"wp-image-16355936\" style=\"width:513px;height:478px\" width=\"513\" height=\"478\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-main.png 1026w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-main-300x280.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-main-1024x954.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-main-768x716.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 513px) 100vw, 513px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To add the <em>Query Loop </em>block to a page, click the <strong>block inserter</strong> (+) icon to open the block inserter pop-up window and choose the <em>Query Loop</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1440\" height=\"668\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/adding-query-loop-pattern.gif\" alt=\"Adding a query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355937\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use the keyboard shortcut <kbd>/query-loop</kbd> to quickly insert a <em>Query Loop</em> block.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f4fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block configuration</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>After adding the <em>Query Loop</em> block you will see two options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Choose</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Start blank</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/placeholder-1.png\" alt=\"Query loop block placeholder\" class=\"wp-image-16355938\" style=\"width:657px;height:209px\" width=\"657\" height=\"209\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/placeholder-1.png 1314w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/placeholder-1-300x95.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/placeholder-1-1024x326.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/placeholder-1-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to choose a pattern</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you select the <em>Choose</em> option, you will have various pattern options. Just select one that you like, and it will be added. Each<em> Query Loop block</em> is made up of various nested blocks, like the <em>Post Title block</em> and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/pagination-block/\"><em>Pagination block</em></a>, so depending on which pattern you choose, nested blocks can differ.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1486\" height=\"980\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-pattern.png\" alt=\"Choosing a query loop block pattern\" class=\"wp-image-16355939\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-pattern.png 1486w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-pattern-300x198.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-pattern-1024x675.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-pattern-768x506.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1486px) 100vw, 1486px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to start blank</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you select the <em>Start blank</em> option, you\u2019ll see four variations you can choose from. Select the one you want to use.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1430\" height=\"674\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/adding-blank-query-loop.gif\" alt=\"Adding a blank query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355940\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to customize the appearance</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are numerous ways to customize the <em>Query Loop block,</em> partially because it\u2019s made up of nested blocks that you can rearrange, add to, and more. When you customize one block in the <em>Query Loop block</em>, the changes will apply to all blocks of the same type. While customizing this block, it might help to use the List View found in the top toolbar. Here are some ideas for customization to get you started:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You can <strong>change the width</strong> of various aspects of the <em>Query Loop block</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can <strong>change the alignmen</strong>t of blocks within the <em>Query Loop</em> <em>block.</em></li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can <strong>add blocks</strong> into the <em>Query Loop block</em>, like <em>Post Author</em> or <em>Post Excerpt</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can <strong>rearrange the blocks</strong> to your liking, dragging and dropping or using the movers to do so.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can <strong>change the number of posts </strong>listed by selecting the <em>Query Loop block</em> and adjusting the Display Settings option in the block toolbar.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can <strong>set various color options</strong> for the nested blocks.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can <strong>add featured images</strong> by adding the <em>Featured Image block</em>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>It\u2019s also possible to add text or blocks when the <em>Query Loop</em> block returns no results:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1999\" height=\"1129\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/no-results.png\" alt=\"No results text for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355941\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/no-results.png 1999w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/no-results-300x169.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/no-results-1024x578.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/no-results-768x434.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/no-results-1536x868.png 1536w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1999px) 100vw, 1999px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To view the block toolbar, click on the block, and the toolbar will be displayed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block has unique toolbar icons and blocks specific user controls that allow you to manipulate the block right in the editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Query Loop</em> block shows nine buttons in the block toolbar:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/toolbar-2.png\" alt=\"Query loop block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16355942\" style=\"width:425px;height:57px\" width=\"425\" height=\"57\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/toolbar-2.png 850w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/toolbar-2-300x40.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/toolbar-2-768x103.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 425px) 100vw, 425px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Transform to</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Drag icon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Move arrows</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Align</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Display settings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Replace</li>\n\n\n\n<li>List view/Grid view</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More options</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Transform to</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-4.png\" alt=\"Transform to tool for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355944\" style=\"width:439px;height:205px\" width=\"439\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-4.png 878w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-4-300x140.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/transform-4-768x359.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 439px) 100vw, 439px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on the \u201cTransform\u201d button to convert the <em>Query Loop</em> block into a \u201cGroup\u201d or \u201cColumns\u201d block.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Drag icon</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/drag-and-drop.png\" alt=\"Drag tool for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355945\" style=\"width:424px;height:56px\" width=\"424\" height=\"56\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/drag-and-drop.png 848w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/drag-and-drop-300x40.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/drag-and-drop-768x101.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To drag and drop the block to a new location on the page template, click and hold the rectangle of dots, then drag it to the new location. The blue separator line indicates where the block will be placed. Release the left mouse button when you find the new location to place the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Move arrows</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/arrows-2.png\" alt=\"Move handles for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355946\" style=\"width:423px;height:58px\" width=\"423\" height=\"58\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/arrows-2.png 846w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/arrows-2-300x41.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/arrows-2-768x105.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 423px) 100vw, 423px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The up and down arrow icons can be used to move the block up and down on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f4fa\">Detailed instructions on moving a block within the editor can be found <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/moving-blocks/\">here</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Align</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-alignment.png\" alt=\"Alignment tool for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355947\" style=\"width:435px;height:217px\" width=\"435\" height=\"217\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-alignment.png 870w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-alignment-300x150.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-alignment-768x383.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the change alignment tool to align the <em>Query Loop </em>block. Choose one of the following options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>None \u2013 </strong>leaves the block the current size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wide width \u2013 </strong>increase the width of the block beyond the content size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Full width \u2013 </strong>extend the block to cover the full width of the screen.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The \u201cWide width\u201d and \u201cFull width\u201d alignment settings must be enabled by your WordPress theme.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Display settings</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/display-settings.png\" alt=\"Display settings for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355948\" style=\"width:435px;height:279px\" width=\"435\" height=\"279\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/display-settings.png 870w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/display-settings-300x192.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/display-settings-768x493.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the display settings tool to change various options for the <em>Query Loop </em>block. Choose one of the following options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Items per Page</strong> \u2013 Choose how many posts you want to show within the <em>Query Loop block</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Offset</strong> \u2013 Enable the <em>Query Loop block</em> to skip a certain number of WordPress posts before starting output.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Max page to show</strong> \u2013 Limits how many pieces of content to show.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you don\u2019t see this section, it\u2019s because you need to toggle off the \u201cInherit query from template\u201d setting.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Replace</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/replace.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-16355949\" style=\"width:427px;height:60px\" width=\"427\" height=\"60\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/replace.png 854w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/replace-300x42.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/replace-768x108.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 427px) 100vw, 427px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the replace option to replace the current pattern with a new one.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/replace.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">List view (default)</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Displays your post in a stacked list.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/list-view-2-1024x771.png\" alt=\"List view tool for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355951\" style=\"width:615px;height:464px\" width=\"615\" height=\"464\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/list-view-2-1024x771.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/list-view-2-300x226.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/list-view-2-768x578.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/list-view-2.png 1334w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 615px) 100vw, 615px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Grid view</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Displays your posts in a grid view.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/grid-view-1024x550.png\" alt=\"Grid view tool for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355952\" style=\"width:613px;height:329px\" width=\"613\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/grid-view-1024x550.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/grid-view-300x161.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/grid-view-768x412.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/grid-view.png 1326w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 613px) 100vw, 613px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Options</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Options button on a block toolbar gives you more features to customize the block.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f4fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Block Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The block settings panel contains customization options specific to the block. To open it, select the block and click the settings icon next to the <strong>Publish/Update </strong>button.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-settings-1.png\" alt=\"Block settings button in the editor\" class=\"wp-image-16355954\" style=\"width:494px;height:74px\" width=\"494\" height=\"74\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-settings-1.png 658w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/block-settings-1-300x45.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 494px) 100vw, 494px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are the options for the <em>Query Loop </em>block:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Color</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Starting from WordPress 6.2, the Query Loop block will no longer support color settings. As a result, you will need to change the colors of the individual blocks that are within the <em>Query Loop</em><strong><em> </em></strong>block instead:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1999\" height=\"1092\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/color.png\" alt=\"Customizing query loop block color\" class=\"wp-image-16355955\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/color.png 1999w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/color-300x164.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/color-1024x559.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/color-768x420.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/color-1536x839.png 1536w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1999px) 100vw, 1999px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f4fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">See this guide for more information about changing colors.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Inner blocks use content width</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This option allows you to configure justification, content, and wide width settings for all nested blocks within the Query<em> Loop</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1440\" height=\"668\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-layout-settings.gif\" alt=\"Customizing query loop block with content width\" class=\"wp-image-16355956\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Inherit query from template</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is an option you can toggle on and off, depending on whether you want to customize the query the loop relies upon. WordPress will otherwise rely on the template being used to determine what posts appear. If you toggle it on, certain customization options will be hidden. If you toggle it off, more customization options will appear.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Post type</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress contains different types of content, and they are divided into collections called \u201cPost types\u201d. By default, there are a few different ones, such as blog posts and pages, but plugins could add more.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Order by</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Newest to Oldest (default)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Oldest to Newest</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Alphabetical A to Z</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Alphabetical Z to A</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Sticky posts</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This option allows you to choose between three options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Include (default) \u2013 Displays sticky posts.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Exclude \u2013 Removes sticky posts.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Only \u2013 Shows only sticky posts.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Filters</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This option allows you to customize further what posts are being displayed. If you don\u2019t see this section, it\u2019s because you need to toggle off the \u201cInherit query from template\u201d setting.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"342\" height=\"668\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/query-loop-filters.gif\" alt=\"Filtering query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355957\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Categories \u2013 </strong>List any categories you want included.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tags \u2013 </strong>List any tags you want included.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Authors \u2013 </strong>Search for an author and add it to the list, multiple authors are allowed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Keyword \u2013 </strong>Enter any keywords you want included.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Mind that custom taxonomies filtering is also possible. Check the following example for the WooCommerce product categories filter:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/product.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you choose a hierarchical post type like Page, these options will be shown:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Authors \u2013 </strong>Search for an author and add it to the list, multiple authors are allowed.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Keyword \u2013 </strong>Enter any keywords you want included.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Parents</strong> <strong>\u2013 </strong>List any parents you want included.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/page.mov\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Advanced Settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The advanced tab lets you add a CSS class to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit. It also allows you to assign an HTML element.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/advanced-2.png\" alt=\"Advanced settings for query loop block\" class=\"wp-image-16355958\" style=\"width:404px;height:320px\" width=\"404\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/advanced-2.png 538w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/03/advanced-2-300x238.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 404px) 100vw, 404px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Resources</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wptavern.com/query-loop-the-ins-and-outs-of-one-of-wordpress-5-8s-most-powerful-features\">Query Loop: The Ins and Outs of One of WordPress 5.8\u2019s Most Powerful Features</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-03-26\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Revised formatting for the whole article</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added videos/screenshots where applicable&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated Block Settings Color section</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated Filters section flow along with new parent filter, multiple author, and custom taxonomies filtering&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated block creation and replacement flows</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added a mention and a screenshot on customizing what is shown when the Query Loop block shows no results</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added a link to Pagination block</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated all the screenshots for 6.2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added in resources section on 2021-07-14</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Created</strong> 2021-07-08 </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
